title: Feid - el único tema del ferxxo (Official Live Performance) | Vevo
description:
Feid - el único tema del ferxxo (Official Live Performance)  | Vevo

Cuando Vevo nombró a Feid como uno de sus DSCVR Artists to Watch en el 2017, teníamos altas expectativas en cuanto a su éxito. Hoy día, estamos súper emocionados de ver a cientos de miles de fans recibiendo al medallo en estadios alrededor de Estados Unidos y Latinoamérica vestidos de verde neón y portando las clásicas Oakleys blancas de Feid. Su imagen se ha convertido en un ícono mundial de la cultura nea: sliders con calcetines, camisas extra grandes, pantalones cortos y AirForce1s. El sonido que ha cultivado se ha convertido emblemático del reggaetón de Medellín, y su carisma le ha ganado el amor de sus fans y compañeros en la industria. El colombiano la mantiene 100% real. Haciendo de tripas corazones, convirtió el robo de su disco ‘Feliz Cumpleaños Ferxxo:Te Pirateamos el Álbum’ en todo un evento que le consiguió su primer Top 10 en la lista Billboard Latin Albums y una gira todo vendido. Su sexto álbum de estudio, ‘Mor, no le temas a la oscuridad’, se convirtió en el más grande de su carrera, debutando en el No.4 en la lista Billboard Latin Albums. title: Feid - HECTOL (Live Session) | Vevo Ctrl
description:
Feid -  HECTOL - Live Session | Vevo Ctrl

It’s wild how fast a new artist can rise when their skills are deep and their work ethic powerful. We chose Feid to be part of our DSCVR: Artists To Watch in 2018 because we knew that the then-newcomer to the Latin music scene had both qualities mentioned above. It didn’t take long for the Medellin native to prove us right. The DSCVR co-sign he got from Nacho was followed by a barrage of features and collabs from and with reggaeton’s best and brightest. By the time Feid’s ‘FERXX0 (Vol 1: M.O.R)’ album arrived last year, he’d been hanging with everyone from Sech to Maluma to Sky to Balvin (he co-wrote the Colombian superstar’s “Ginza”) to...you get the point. Which is that Feid has arrived. His new “TENGO FE” and “FUMETEO” are the work of a daring pro, not an edgy newcomer - you can hear it throughout his third album, 'Intershibuya - La Mafia.' When he arrived at our Brooklyn Ctrl studio, he was ready for business. Both “HECTOL” and "TENGO FE" resound with all the authority you’d expect from a deep talent.  

Watch the TENGO FE official video: https://youtu.be/e9o6QNrtxm0

title: Feid - TENGO FE (Live Session) | Vevo Ctrl
description:
Feid - TENGO FE - Live Session | Vevo Ctrl

It’s wild how fast a new artist can rise when their skills are deep and their work ethic powerful. We chose Feid to be part of our DSCVR: Artists To Watch in 2018 because we knew that the then-newcomer to the Latin music scene had both qualities mentioned above. It didn’t take long for the Medellin native to prove us right. The DSCVR co-sign he got from Nacho was followed by a barrage of features and collabs from and with reggaeton’s best and brightest. By the time Feid’s ‘FERXX0 (Vol 1: M.O.R)’ album arrived last year, he’d been hanging with everyone from Sech to Maluma to Sky to Balvin (he co-wrote the Colombian superstar’s “Ginza”) to...you get the point. Which is that Feid has arrived. His new “Tengo Fe” and “Fumeteo” are the work of a daring pro, not an edgy newcomer. His 'Intershibuya - La Mafia' album should grace us before the end of 2021. When he arrived at our Brooklyn Ctrl studio, he was ready for business. Both “HECTOL” and "TENGO FE" resound with all the authority you’d expect from a deep talent.

El cantante Colombiano Feid explora el lado bueno y el malo de un amor con ritmos de R&B en “Buena/Mala.”

Feid es un cantante del género Urbano Latino. Otros de sus éxitos han sido “Que raro” con J. Balvin, “911” con Nacho, “Lluvia”, “Perfecta” con Greeicy, “Nuestra Canción” y “Sigueme”; la cual tuvo un remix con Tech.

Ademas de ser cantante, Feid también es cantante y compositor y ha sido parte del éxito de canciones como “Ginza” de J. Balvin y “Mamita” de CNCO.
